  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I give my girlfriend space / stop the feeling of having my soul sucked out for the seconds I'm not with her?",
  "response": "It's completely normal to feel deeply connected to your girlfriend and want to spend a lot of time with her, especially if you're in a new or passionate phase of your relationship. However, it's also important to respect both her need for space and your own well-being. Here are a few suggestions to help you navigate this:\n\n1. **Acknowledge Your Feelings**: Recognize that intense emotions are natural, but try not to let them control your actions. Simply being aware of your feelings is the first step to managing them.\n\n2. **Focus on Self-Care**: Use the time apart to focus on your own interests and hobbies. This can be a healthy distraction and also makes you a more interesting and well-rounded partner.\n\n3. **Set Personal Goals**: Pursue goals that are important to you, whether they\u2019re career-related, personal development, or a new skill. This will help you build your own identity outside of the relationship.\n\n4. **Stay Connected in Moderation**: While it's important to give her space, you can still stay connected. Send a thoughtful message or check in with her, but balance it so that it doesn\u2019t feel overwhelming.\n\n5. **Practice Mindfulness**: Engage in mindfulness exercises such as meditation or deep breathing. These can help reduce feelings of anxiety or neediness when you\u2019re not with her.\n\n6. **Cultivate Other Relationships**: Spend time with friends and family. This helps ensure your emotional needs aren\u2019t solely dependent on your girlfriend.\n\n7. **Communicate Openly**: Talk with your girlfriend about your feelings. Be honest but also respectful of her needs. This can often bring reassurance and clarity.\n\n8. **Develop Emotional Independence**: Work on being comfortable with solitude and your own company. This will give you strength within the relationship and outside of it.\n\n9. **Reflect on the Relationship**: Consider why you feel the way you do. Are there underlying insecurities or fears of losing her? Understanding these can be crucial to addressing them.\n\nRemember that a healthy relationship usually involves both closeness and independence. By working on these aspects, you can likely find a balance that will be fulfilling for both you and your girlfriend.",
